defaultCommunity transport is of ever increasing importance to isolated communities as it is often used to fill gaps in the public transport network.  It can tak
defaulte many forms with funding ranging from local volunteer fund raising to financial support from local transport authorities.  Community transport is effective by using:-
default&#xa0;
defaulta)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultVehicles which are suited to the route(s) needed and the
default groups of passengers using the 
defaultservices and may be also be more affordable where local fund raising provides the vehicle
default.
defaultb)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThere can be a greater degree of flexibility for services arranged at local level
default.
defaultc)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultConsideration should be given to raising the age odefaultf volunteer drivers from 70 to 75, subject to health and driver ability tests.default&#xa0;
defaultTaxis and other demand responsive services
default are expensive to use by those living in isolated communities.  Often these people are those whose circumstances have changed with the passage of time and they are no longer able to drive or have the use of a car.  All groups of passengers in these circums
defaulttances can have widely diverse needs which make resolving the challenges more demanding.  Many living in isolated communities do so in the knowledge that public transport is likely to be limited.
defaultCar schemes (often used for medical appointments) and innova
defaulttive use of taxis are two approaches which can contribute to the easing of travel costs.
defaultOlder people may find the need to move to urban areas to ease the cost of travel.  Young people of working age may also need to more away from rural areas for similar 
defaultreasons.  This has a social impact on the sustainability of villages and hamlets in remote areas.
default&#xa0;
