defaultSubject to finance availability, improve the travel experience quality for users of public transport by extending to use of “Real Time Information” for buses and “Customer Information System” for rail.  These measures together with the wider av
defaultailability of shelters, seating and time tables at all stops, may also go some way to persuading car users to change their travel habits
default.
default&#xa0;defaultConclusiondefault   Local knowledge, together with research amongst Senior Voice Devon members and local Councillors and O
defaultfficers, has enabled us to answer the questions often in a positive light.  We are fortunate in having a County Council where both Councillors and Officers take a detailed interest in all forms of public transport.  We have noted they are willing to “look 
defaultoutside the box” and to experiment.  They work closely with bus companies, both large and small, and have taken the lead in encouraging and being directly involved in all the Devon rail branch lines becoming 
defaultmembers of the Community Rail Partnership.  Whil
defaultst there will always be room for improvement and some necessary adjustment of bus routes and timetabling, we note that since April 2012 only one bus service in Devon has been withdrawn entirely.
